- `InductiveMerkleTree.buildMerkleTree` is a monadic function that builds a full binary tree using an oracle function implicitly defined in its structure.
- `InductiveMerkleTree.buildMerkleTree_with_hash` is a functional (non-monadic) version of the same construction, taking an explicit hash function (oracle) as an argument.
- `runWithOracle f` applies the oracle function `f` to the result of a monadic computation.

The theorem is essentially saying that the monadic and functional versions of the tree construction are equivalent when using the same underlying hash function.

